Shankara, an Indian philosopher, probably lived in the 8th century CE.
He taught the unity of the soul and God, the 'Advaita' (non-dualistic)
branch of Vedanta Hinduism. This is a short sampler of some of his
important texts, originally published as a Sanskrit primer with each
verse also given in Sanskrit. This etext includes the English
translation only.--<span class="small">J.B. Hare, December 28th,
2008.</span>

